    public interface Aggregate<K,V>
extends java.lang.Iterable<V>, View<V>, Receiver
    Core aggregation interface. Aggregates are described in terms of member elements. An element is a logical (key, value) pair, with standard generic templates of <K, V>. Aggregate is-a Iterable of its element (V) values and has-a Set of its element (K) keys.

    Aggregates provide a minimal, single hierarchical view of collections and are intended to work in conjunction with (supplement) the Java Collections Framework (JCF), not to replace it. Implementors must ensure that extensions do not conflict with (break) the JCF interfaces.

    When an Aggregate is an Vector-based aggregation, the element key is referred to as the element's index. When the aggregation is Composed, the element's key is referred to as the element's selector.

    Mutation methods in this hierarchy follow the general approach of the JCF with regards to being optionally supported operations. Additionally, some aggregates support the concept of being in alterable/non-alterable state. When an alteration message is received by a supported operation, and the aggregate is not in alterable state, an IllegalStateException is to be thrown.

      • set

        V set(K aKey,
      V aValue)
        Associates aValue or null to an element of this aggregation. Whether the element is created, modified, or removed is not defined by this interface.

        Sub-interfaces or implementations may throw exceptions in addition to those specified here.

        Parameters:
        aKey - The element's key. When a non-null key would be added to the key set then keys().getElementType().isInstance(aKey) must answer true. This interfaces doesn't specify whether a null key is allowed.
        aValue - The element's value or null. getElementType().isInstance(aValue) must answer true for a non-null value.
        Returns:
        The prior value held by the element when applicable or null when not.
        Throws:
        java.lang.UnsupportedOperationException - When modification is not supported by this aggregation.
        java.lang.NullPointerException - When the specified key or value is null and this aggregation does not permit null keys or values.
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - When some aspect of the specified key or value prevents the value being stored.
        java.lang.IllegalStateException - When the current state of this object prevents a modification.

      • size

        int size()
        Returns:
        Return the size of this Aggregate or Integer.MAX_VALUE when the count of elements exceeds an integer range.
